<DOC><DOCNO> AP880506-0143 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-06-88 1323EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Germany-USCrash 1stLd-Writethru   05-06 0180</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Germany-US Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0634,0182</SECOND><HEAD>URGENT</HEAD><HEAD>U.S. Military Helicopter Crashes At Air Show</HEAD><NOTE>EDS: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with two killed, CORRECTS thathelicopter is British but U.S.-made. No pickup</NOTE><DATELINE>HANOVER, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A British military helicoptercrashed and burst into flames at an international air show today,killing at least two people and injuring several others, officialssaid.   Airport officials in Hanover said the crash occurred as thehelicopter returned from a short demonstration flight. They saidthe helicopter hit a loading ramp at the airport with its backrotor.   In early reports, eyewitnesses said the helicopter belonged tothe U.S. military, but airport officials later said the aircraftwas a U.S.-made Chinook helicopter flown by the British.   The accident occurred at about 6 p.m. (12 noon EDT) shortlyafter the end of the air show, officials said.   It was not immediately known whether the dead were members ofthe crew or whether there were fatalities on the ground.   Fire and emergency crews raced to the scene after the crash,pouring foam on the burning wreckage.</TEXT></DOC>